Package inkball

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Drawable
    The Drawable interface should be implemented by any class whose instances are intended to be drawn in the Inkball game.
    Movable
    The Movable interface should be implemented by any class whose instances are intended to move or change position in the Inkball game.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccelerateTile
    Represents an acceleration tile that speeds up the ball in a specific direction when it passes over.
    App  
    Ball
    Represents a ball entity in the Inkball game.
    ColorUtils
    Utility class for converting between color names and their corresponding numbers.
    ConfigReader
    The ConfigReader class is responsible for reading and managing game settings from a configuration JSON file.
    Entity
    The Entity class serves as an abstract base class for all objects in the Inkball game that have a position (x, y) and a color.
    Hole
    Represents a Hole object in the Inkball game.
    Level
    The Level class manages the entities and layout of a specific game level.
    PlayerDrawnLine
    The PlayerDrawnLine class represents a line drawn by the player in the Inkball game.
    Spawner
    The Spawner class represents a spawning point in the Inkball game where balls are generated.
    Wall
    The Wall class represents a wall in the Inkball game.
    YellowTile
    The YellowTile class represents a yellow tile that moves around the perimeter of the game board.
